      • registerScheduledTask

        public void registerScheduledTask(String name,
                                  Runnable task,
                                  long period)
        Used by object to register tasks to be executed at defined interval Each task will be given it's own thread at execution.
        Parameters:
        name - the name that will be given to the thread when running
        task - the task to execute in it's dedicated thread
        period - time in milliseconds between successive task executions.
